Third.

110
00:09:24,814 --> 00:09:25,982
Third, start the engine!

111
00:09:26,065 --> 00:09:26,983
Again.

112
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:28,150
Brakes.

113
00:09:29,277 --> 00:09:30,361
Start the engine.

114
00:09:32,947 --> 00:09:35,449
We're pretty much crawling.

115
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:38,744
That's my report!

116
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:40,538
Wait! Come on!

117
00:09:40,621 --> 00:09:41,747
Disqualified.

118
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:46,627
-Hu!
-What is it?

119
00:09:46,711 --> 00:09:48,713
Are you seriously keeping an eye on me?

120
00:09:48,796 --> 00:09:49,755
What?

121
00:09:50,131 --> 00:09:52,842
Can't you see that I'm doing my best

122
00:09:52,925 --> 00:09:54,844
to help you drive here?

123
00:09:55,303 --> 00:09:56,679
Why do I sound like this?

124
00:09:56,804 --> 00:09:59,932
I'm trying so hard to help you.

125
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:01,642
Then you should've told me earlier!

126
00:10:01,726 --> 00:10:04,353
Thanks to you, I'm already disqualified!

127
00:10:10,693 --> 00:10:13,154
There. Remember the steps and begin.

128
00:10:13,237 --> 00:10:15,865
How could an angel threaten someone
and adopt an expedient?

129
00:10:15,948 --> 00:10:16,991
Begin.

130
00:10:17,825 --> 00:10:19,994
-Fine.
-Are you ready? Begin.

131
00:10:20,077 --> 00:10:21,746
-No!
-Hey, hey!

132
00:10:21,829 --> 00:10:23,748
Do it again.

133
00:10:23,831 --> 00:10:24,832
Which one's the accelerator?

134
00:10:24,915 --> 00:10:27,001
-The right side!
-Here I go.

135
00:10:27,084 --> 00:10:28,961
-Good, good!
-Good, good!

136
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:31,172
-Which one's the brakes?
-Stop!

137
00:10:31,255 --> 00:10:33,257
Make it go back again!

138
00:10:36,844 --> 00:10:38,095
Why is it going this way?

139
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:43,809
Stop! You did it!

140
00:10:45,811 --> 00:10:47,063
No wonder you always cause trouble.

141
00:10:47,146 --> 00:10:48,939
You're not smart, to begin with.

142
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:52,193
I'm never going to learn
anything from you!

143
00:10:53,152 --> 00:10:54,320
You little...

144
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:57,573
Hey, Dan.

145
00:10:58,783 --> 00:10:59,617
Dan!

146
00:11:00,409 --> 00:11:02,370
You're pretty much a human now.

147
00:11:02,453 --> 00:11:03,704
You're actually angry.

148
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:05,915
You were too harsh! It was my first time!

149
00:11:05,998 --> 00:11:07,416
-Goodness.
-I didn't know anything.

150
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,085
I didn't know what I was doing.

151
00:11:09,168 --> 00:11:11,087
But you shouted and criticized me!

152
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:12,713
I wasn't happy with what you were doing,

153
00:11:12,797 --> 00:11:14,006
so I wanted you to snap out of it.

154
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:15,883
Animals were your only clients.

155
00:11:15,966 --> 00:11:18,427
I was worried you wouldn't know which way

156
00:11:18,511 --> 00:11:21,263
to lead your human client
and ultimately fail.

157
00:11:21,347 --> 00:11:22,264
What do you mean?

158
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:24,392
I know this is your first
time dealing with humans.

159
00:11:24,475 --> 00:11:26,060
This is your first time
in a human body too.

160
00:11:26,143 --> 00:11:29,814
But still, don't you think
this was a bit too much?

161
00:11:29,897 --> 00:11:30,815
Listen to this.

162
00:11:30,898 --> 00:11:32,942
"Lee Yeon-seo danced.

163
00:11:33,067 --> 00:11:34,860
She was beautiful.

164
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:37,196
It was the prettiest thing

165
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:38,906
I saw on earth."

166
00:11:39,448 --> 00:11:41,117
She overworked herself.

167
00:11:41,742 --> 00:11:42,618
I was scared

168
00:11:43,285 --> 00:11:46,038
that she'd suffer and become unhappy.

169
00:11:46,747 --> 00:11:50,167
But when she was dancing, her face glowed.

170
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:52,503
She was definitely happy.

171
00:11:54,046 --> 00:11:56,799
How many times did you mention her?

172
00:11:56,882 --> 00:11:57,925
There are 20 lines about her.

173
00:11:58,008 --> 00:12:00,886
In the end, you wrote, "She hugged Rib."

174
00:12:00,970 --> 00:12:03,055
It was just that one sentence.

175
00:12:03,139 --> 00:12:05,141
What kind of report is this?

176
00:12:05,850 --> 00:12:07,268
It's the truth!

177
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:09,979
Since we're talking about it,
I have a question.

178
00:12:10,229 --> 00:12:12,064
Do you think he's a strong one?

179
00:12:12,148 --> 00:12:13,190
What are you saying?

180
00:12:14,483 --> 00:12:15,484
Her life has just begun!

181
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:20,030
She needs a strong, good rib beside her
for her to become happy.

182
00:12:23,576 --> 00:12:24,452
Could you

183
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:26,579
look into it for me?

184
00:12:45,014 --> 00:12:47,349
THE LATE CHOI SEOL-HUI

185
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:16,670
Are you scared?

186
00:13:17,046 --> 00:13:18,464
Well. No.

187
00:13:20,090 --> 00:13:21,467
I'll be with you.

188
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:43,697
-Kang-woo.
-It's dangerous.

189
00:13:44,365 --> 00:13:45,324
Stay back.

190
00:14:04,635 --> 00:14:06,720
Listen, Angel Raporas.

191
00:14:07,346 --> 00:14:11,141
You had received a mission of
inspiring artists

192
00:14:11,225 --> 00:14:15,396
so that they would be able to draw things
that would give joy to the deity.

193
00:14:15,688 --> 00:14:19,024
However, you betrayed your mission
and even decided to abandon the deity.

194
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:21,527
Therefore, you will be judged.

195
00:14:21,610 --> 00:14:23,529
I've fulfilled my mission as an angel.

196
00:14:24,446 --> 00:14:25,531
From now on,

197
00:14:26,949 --> 00:14:28,784
I'd like to become a muse

198
00:14:30,661 --> 00:14:31,620
for one person only.

199
00:14:47,261 --> 00:14:48,679
Becoming an angel,

200
00:14:49,179 --> 00:14:50,598
becoming a human,

201
00:14:51,682 --> 00:14:53,434
starting a life,

202
00:14:54,476 --> 00:14:55,644
and ending a life

203
00:14:57,271 --> 00:14:59,106
all depend on the deity's will.

204
00:15:01,901 --> 00:15:02,985
Don't come.

205
00:15:04,153 --> 00:15:05,362
Don't come. Please.

206
00:15:11,535 --> 00:15:12,953
This is cruel.

207
00:15:14,038 --> 00:15:14,997
Then

208
00:15:15,748 --> 00:15:17,166
why did the deity give me a heart?

209
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:18,709
Giving me a heart

210
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:21,128
and telling me to overcome my feelings

211
00:15:22,421 --> 00:15:24,173
are the doings of a devil!

212
00:15:24,298 --> 00:15:26,759
I will take everything
that the deity has given

213
00:15:27,343 --> 00:15:28,427
from you.

214
00:16:30,364 --> 00:16:31,240
Please, no.

215
00:16:31,323 --> 00:16:32,282
Please.

216
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:34,910
Please.

217
00:16:40,165 --> 00:16:41,166
Please.

218
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:35,596
THE LATE CHOI SEOL-HUI

219
00:17:45,022 --> 00:17:47,191
I desperately wanted to become a human,

220
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:50,027
but not in the world

221
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:52,321
where you don't exist.

222
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:34,530
I could neither die

223
00:18:35,531 --> 00:18:36,949
nor live a proper life.

224
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:39,785
I was lost for 15 years.

225
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:46,959
I think

226
00:18:49,461 --> 00:18:50,838
it will work out really well this time.

227
00:18:53,006 --> 00:18:55,801
You must have lost someone dear to you.

228
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:59,555
I can still see waves
of yearning in your eyes.

229
00:18:59,721 --> 00:19:01,431
As you loved the person
with all of your heart,

230
00:19:01,515 --> 00:19:03,100
I am sure your loved one
will be in paradise.

231
00:19:03,392 --> 00:19:06,270
And I can only assume
that she will be in peace.

232
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:10,691
Does "peace" really exist?

233
00:19:12,276 --> 00:19:13,485
Living is already a torment.

234
00:19:13,944 --> 00:19:15,779
Wishing to be born again
is a silly thought.

235
00:19:15,863 --> 00:19:18,157
And wishing for peace on the other side

236
00:19:19,366 --> 00:19:20,534
sounds lame, doesn't it?

237
00:19:23,662 --> 00:19:24,663
Then,

238
00:19:26,748 --> 00:19:28,500
what is it that you want?

239
00:19:45,058 --> 00:19:46,351
Will you really attend the event?

240
00:19:48,270 --> 00:19:49,938
"If you leave your home,
there will be trouble.

241
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:50,898
Stay at home."

242
00:19:51,565 --> 00:19:52,900
That's your horoscope for today.

243
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:54,401
Doesn't this sound too eerie?

244
00:19:54,484 --> 00:19:56,320
One person warns me with some saying.

245
00:19:56,653 --> 00:19:57,946
And the other with my horoscope.

246
00:19:58,030 --> 00:19:59,531
It's because
we don't feel good about this.

247
00:19:59,615 --> 00:20:00,532
Horoscopes are big data

248
00:20:00,616 --> 00:20:03,410
that contain the principles of
the universe and human history.

249
00:20:03,493 --> 00:20:06,747
-If you ignore it, you'll be in trouble.
-I'll face it.

250
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:08,832
I probably can't avoid it
even if I want to.

251
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:13,962
Fine.

252
00:20:14,504 --> 00:20:15,672
If you're going to attend,

253
00:20:15,756 --> 00:20:18,217
might as well go and announce it
with a bright smile.

254
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:21,720
"Fantasia belongs to me. This is where
I should be." Make it official.

255
00:20:22,846 --> 00:20:24,014
I'll be out after I get changed.

256
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:26,516
Okay.

257
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:45,035
Do you like me?

258
00:20:45,577 --> 00:20:46,870
Just say yes or no.

259
00:20:49,414 --> 00:20:50,415
Did you like me?

260
00:20:52,668 --> 00:20:54,670
Do you?

261
00:20:58,799 --> 00:20:59,800
No.

262
00:21:11,645 --> 00:21:13,313
Hello. What would you like?

263
00:21:13,397 --> 00:21:15,357
Something to help me be okay on my own.

264
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:16,650
-Pardon?
-Relaxing pills,

265
00:21:16,733 --> 00:21:18,402
sedatives, or stimulant drugs.

266
00:21:18,860 --> 00:21:20,112
I don't care what it is.

267
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:22,364
I've been

268
00:21:23,115 --> 00:21:24,700
relying on people too much.

269
00:21:26,034 --> 00:21:28,745
I've been relying on a guy
who doesn't even like me.

270
00:21:29,705 --> 00:21:32,416
I'm not the type of person
who easily gets attached.

271
00:21:34,876 --> 00:21:36,670
I must have lost my mind
for a second or something.

272
00:21:37,129 --> 00:21:38,130
Give me some medicine

273
00:21:38,463 --> 00:21:40,048
that will make me be okay
